## AI components

> Every AI component in the product. AI Tech Lead defaults to these patterns — override if you've chosen differently.

- **LLM:** Anthropic Claude via `@anthropic-ai/sdk` — `claude-sonnet-4-6` as default model
- **Embeddings:** `text-embedding-3-small` via OpenAI SDK
- **Vector store:** pgvector on Supabase
- **Prompt location:** `src/ai/prompts/` — one file per prompt, named functions only
- **Output schemas:** `src/ai/schemas/` — Zod schemas, validated before use
- **AI client:** `src/ai/client.ts` — single Anthropic client with timeout + retry
- **Evals:** `src/ai/evals/` — see `templates/eval-starter.md` for structure
- **Model fallback:** claude-haiku-4-5 if latency budget exceeded

---

## Architecture

- Next.js monorepo — frontend and API in one repo
- AI services isolated in `src/ai/` — client, prompts, schemas, evals
- Database access via Supabase client — no raw SQL unless pgvector queries
- All AI calls go through `src/ai/client.ts` — never call Anthropic SDK directly in components

---

## Rules

> Only add rules for things AI Tech Lead gets wrong without being told.

1. All AI prompts in `src/ai/prompts/` — never inlined in business logic
2. All AI outputs validated with Zod schema before use — never trust raw LLM output
3. Every AI endpoint has a timeout, rate limit, and fallback
4. PII stripped before sending any user data to AI APIs
5. TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no `as unknown as`
6. Server components by default — client components only when interactivity required
